Both deliverables emitted in the bundle directory and the transcript validates against `transcript_schema.json` (25 iterations, 31 hypotheses, 31 analyses).

**Headline result:** `feature_008` (binary, 40% prevalence) is the treatment-like variable. Its effect on `objective_response` is concentrated entirely in the subgroup S* = {`feature_013`=0 AND `feature_021`=0 AND `feature_015`=0 AND `feature_027`=0} (n=15,681; 31% of cohort): 17.2% → 79.8% response (RD +62.6 pp, OR ~19). Outside S* the effect is essentially null (RD < 1 pp). All four modifiers act as redundant off-switches; none of the other 27 features modifies the treatment effect. Independent T-learner + decision-tree subgroup discovery rediscovered the same four modifiers.
